.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-REPLAY" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-replay \- Replay a tracked job timeline from runtime artifacts
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose replay [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Reconstruct a best\-effort timeline from tracked state, service\-exit markers, metrics JSONL, and logs, then replay it in the watch\-style terminal UI or print a static summary.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read; if omitted, use the active context compose file or fall back to compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--job\-id\fR \fIJOB_ID\fR
Tracked Slurm job id to replay instead of the latest recorded submission.
.TP
\fB--service\fR \fISERVICE\fR
Service to focus initially and include in the replay.
.TP
\fB--speed\fR \fIMULTIPLIER\fR
Replay speed multiplier, e.g. 1, 10, or 100. Default: 1.
.TP
\fB--lines\fR \fILINES\fR
Number of trailing log lines to seed into the replay view. Default: 100.
.TP
\fB--watch\-mode\fR \fIMODE\fR
Watch output mode. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, tui, line.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format. Possible values: text, json.
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose replay \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose replay \-f compose.yaml \-\-speed 10
hpc\-compose replay \-f compose.yaml \-\-job\-id 12345 \-\-service app
hpc\-compose replay \-f compose.yaml \-\-format json
.fi
